article.headline: Toledo 66, Eastern Michigan 56
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Keonta Howell scored 13 of his 21 points in the second half and Florentino Valencia added 15 Tuesday to rally Toledo to a 66-56 Mid-American Conference victory over Eastern Michigan. It was the 11th straight MAC regular season win for the Rockets (8-8, 4-0). Toledo, the preseason favorite to win the MAC West Division, last lost a conference game Feb. 1, 2006 to Western Michigan. Carlos Medlock and Jesse Bunkley had 18 and 15, respectively, for the Eagles (7-10, 2-2). The loss snapped a two-game winning streak for Eastern Michigan. The game was tied 28-28 at halftime, but Toledo opened the second half with an 11-2 run to go up 39-30. Craig Cashens 3-pointer pulled the Eagles within four with 14:41 to play. The Rockets responded by building their advantage to 51-41 with 9:44 remaining. The Eagles, who committed 23 turnovers, could get no closer than 56-50 with 5:31 left. Eastern Michigan hit eight of its first 10 shots and took an early 19-12 lead. The Eagles, however, made only one of their next nine attempts as the Rockets went on a 12-2 run.
